      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(embedded-runner): expose prep stage timings",
        "body": "## Summary\n- expose existing embedded runner prep stage snapshots on attempt results and run meta\n- include prep stage timings on the `agent_end` hook event for plugin observability\n- add coverage for attempt result and hook event prep stage propagation\n- document the new optional hook field and add an Unreleased changelog entry\n\n## Motivation\nOpenClaw already records detailed embedded runner prep stages internally, but that timing data is not currently available to runtime metadata consumers or plugin hooks. When embedded runs feel slow, plugin authors and operators cannot tell whether time is going into tool bundling, system prompt construction, session resource loading, or stream setup without patching core locally.\n\nExposing the existing stage snapshot gives downstream integrations a stable, low-risk way to collect real latency evidence before proposing behavior-changing optimizations such as tool bundle filtering or prompt caching. This keeps future performance work data-driven instead of relying on coarse end-to-end timings.\n\n## Implementation notes\n- reuses the existing `createEmbeddedRunStageTracker()` / `prepStages.snapshot()` path\n- keeps all new fields optional\n- uses a public structural plugin hook type instead of exporting runner internals through the plugin API\n- does not change tool bundling, system prompt construction, stream setup, model calls, or runner behavior\n- documents `agent_end.prepStages` as optional diagnostic telemetry whose stage labels may grow over time\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Embedded runner prep stage timings are available to runtime metadata consumers and `agent_end` hook observers without changing runner behavior.\n- Real environment tested: Local macOS OpenClaw source checkout at `/Users/guanbear/.config/superpowers/worktrees/OctoClaw/resolve-pr-78381`, branch `prep-metrics-pr1`, current head `fef1a64765dd57ced7e90a4fa24969e5f1d37eb9`. The proof used a temporary `HOME`, `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR`, and `OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH`; a real `openclaw agent --local` embedded run; the repository OpenAI-compatible local response server; and a temporary non-bundled plugin registered through `plugins.load.paths` with `hooks.allowConversationAccess=true`.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```bash\nMOCK_PORT=41xxx SUCCESS_MARKER=OPENCLAW_PREP_PROOF_OK \\\n  MOCK_REQUEST_LOG=/tmp/openclaw-pr78381-proof-JCgOKx/mock-openai.log \\\n  node scripts/e2e/mock-openai-server.mjs\n\nnode scripts/run-node.mjs plugins inspect prep-proof --runtime --json\n\nnode scripts/run-node.mjs agent \\\n  --local \\\n  --agent main \\\n  --session-id prep-proof-session \\\n  --message \"Reply exactly OPENCLAW_PREP_PROOF_OK\" \\\n  --thinking off \\\n  --json\n```\n\n- Evidence after fix: Terminal capture from the current-head runtime proof:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"head\": \"fef1a64765dd57ced7e90a4fa24969e5f1d37eb9\",\n  \"finalAssistantVisibleText\": \"OPENCLAW_PREP_PROOF_OK\",\n  \"metaHasPrepStages\": true,\n  \"metaPrepStages\": {\n    \"totalMs\": 1293,\n    \"stages\": [\n      { \"name\": \"workspace-sandbox\", \"durationMs\": 1, \"elapsedMs\": 1 },\n      { \"name\": \"skills\", \"durationMs\": 0, \"elapsedMs\": 1 },\n      { \"name\": \"core-plugin-tools\", \"durationMs\": 206, \"elapsedMs\": 207 },\n      { \"name\": \"bootstrap-context\", \"durationMs\": 2, \"elapsedMs\": 209 },\n      { \"name\": \"bundle-tools\", \"durationMs\": 151, \"elapsedMs\": 360 },\n      { \"name\": \"system-prompt\", \"durationMs\": 850, \"elapsedMs\": 1210 },\n      { \"name\": \"session-resource-loader\", \"durationMs\": 62, \"elapsedMs\": 1272 },\n      { \"name\": \"agent-session\", \"durationMs\": 2, \"elapsedMs\": 1274 },\n      { \"name\": \"stream-setup\", \"durationMs\": 19, \"elapsedMs\": 1293 }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"hookProof\": {\n    \"success\": true,\n    \"durationMs\": 607,\n    \"hasPrepStages\": true,\n    \"totalMs\": 1293,\n    \"stages\": [\n      { \"name\": \"workspace-sandbox\", \"durationMs\": 1, \"elapsedMs\": 1 },\n      { \"name\": \"skills\", \"durationMs\": 0, \"elapsedMs\": 1 },\n      { \"name\": \"core-plugin-tools\", \"durationMs\": 206, \"elapsedMs\": 207 },\n      { \"name\": \"bootstrap-context\", \"durationMs\": 2, \"elapsedMs\": 209 },\n      { \"name\": \"bundle-tools\", \"durationMs\": 151, \"elapsedMs\": 360 },\n      { \"name\": \"system-prompt\", \"durationMs\": 850, \"elapsedMs\": 1210 },\n      { \"name\": \"session-resource-loader\", \"durationMs\": 62, \"elapsedMs\": 1272 },\n      { \"name\": \"agent-session\", \"durationMs\": 2, \"elapsedMs\": 1274 },\n      { \"name\": \"stream-setup\", \"durationMs\": 19, \"elapsedMs\": 1293 }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"proofLog\": \"/tmp/openclaw-pr78381-proof-JCgOKx/agent-end-prepStages.jsonl\"\n}\n```\n\nThe temporary plugin's raw `agent_end` log line from the same run had `hasPrepStages: true`, `prepStages.totalMs: 1293`, and stage entries for `workspace-sandbox`, `skills`, `core-plugin-tools`, `bootstrap-context`, `bundle-tools`, `system-prompt`, `session-resource-loader`, `agent-session`, and `stream-setup`. The agent command JSON from the same run also included `meta.prepStages` and `finalAssistantVisibleText: \"OPENCLAW_PREP_PROOF_OK\"`, confirming both runtime metadata and the plugin hook observer saw prep-stage telemetry on current head.\n\n- Observed result after fix: A standalone `openclaw agent --local` embedded run completed successfully against the local OpenAI-compatible response server, returned `OPENCLAW_PREP_PROOF_OK`, and the temporary real plugin's `agent_end` handler observed `event.prepStages` with `bundle-tools`, `system-prompt`, and `stream-setup` entries.\n- What was not tested: A live paid external model/provider run was not run; the standalone proof used OpenClaw's deterministic local OpenAI-compatible response server to avoid provider latency/cost while still exercising the real embedded runner, local CLI, plugin loader, and `agent_end` hook dispatch.\n\n## Validation\n- `pnpm test src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/attempt-stage-timing.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/attempt.spawn-workspace.context-engine.test.ts src/plugins/hooks.phase-hooks.test.ts src/plugins/hooks.model-override-wiring.test.ts`\n- `pnpm changed:lanes --json` -> lanes `core`, `coreTests`, `docs`\n- `pnpm check:changed`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n\n",
